				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">new bard ~ needs grouping advice<a name="32672"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 3 04 11:46 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>first of all, i'd like to tip my hat to the people that put this site together... i've done a lot of guide reading (and plan to do more) and it's been a great help
<br />

<br />
where i'm at ~ my main is a necro (L60 on stromm)... i've started a bard alt that i plan to play quite a bit, twinked a bit as you can see from my magelo, but not over-the-top... i plan to level a lot in guildie groups, LDoN and regular campin... not that i won't solo... but it will be a minority of the time
<br />

<br />
i'm currently L22 and my goal by L40 is to be close to max in offense/defense, 1hs, 1hb, piercing so i'll be doing a lot of duel-wield tanking to keep skills up
<br />

<br />
my first question involves twisting while in LDoN and other groups... i pull a lot, so my last four gems are usually lull, bellow (to pull), mez (for mistakes <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-5.gif" border="0" alt="Wink" hspace="2" />) and selo's
<br />

<br />
for the first four, usually chant of battle, jon's whistle (which i know is self only, but seems better than having anthem overwrite chant), heal and manasong... when i start getting my damage shields i'll probably throw that in as a #3 and keep either heal or mana according to need as a #4 (damage shield does not break lull i hope?)
<br />

<br />
for downtime i put in my lute and twist heal/mana, or just one as needed
<br />

<br />
i realize situations may call for changes (a snare for example), but is this a fairly respectable group lineup? i'm really not touching the damage songs at all, should i be?
<br />

<br />
my other question involves stats... is there any specific point to shoot for in dexterity (for missed notes) and charisma (for charm) where you start getting diminishing returns? (thinking about equipment to shoot for here... my main is a smith and i plan to get some veeshan cultural made when i hit my mid-40s)
<br />

<br />
thanks in advance for the advice</span></td>
