				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: new bard ~ needs grouping advice<a name="32921"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 5 04 10:32 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Charisma has a more profound effect on fizzling/missed notes than dexterity does. Though dex does a small effect upon it, dex also effects how often you proc. 
<br />
For grouping at the level your at typically your going to be filling the roles of 2-3 diff classes because groups tend to be slightly imbalanced at that point, so my suggestion would be to evaluate the group skills when you join and memorize a song list that will help support the group and not overwrite abilities already covered. 
<br />
Hence if your missing an enchanter be sure to have your mez's up and ready. If your missing a druid/ranger be sure to have snare up for runners ect ect. Compliment your group and you'll find your talents in versatility will go up also. </span></td>
			</tr><tr>
